Sois tu vas au cours, sois tu lis le livre.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Lecture heavy']

rComments: Terrible prof! Avoid at all costs. Her ppt's are all from the book. The exam is basicaly the book, read and get an A+. She talks slowly and makes you want to fall asleep during the lecture. She loves the subject but she should not be employed by the University.

She's a really nice lady but as a prof she is very boring to listen to! Her lectures are her reading off the slides so you basically don't have to go to class. If you ever have questions though she is very kind and is more than willing to clarify any questions you have!! French Immersion students: lectures easy to understand! final is deadly :(
Exams difficiles, pas de blackboard, lis ses notes en class, pose des questions pas pertinentes pour le cours. YOU NEED TO READ THE BOOK !!!!!

Avoid going to the classes.. Attend the first day and midterms.. that's it. She has boring powerpoints and she reads chapters from the BOOK!! Buy the book and learn on your own time. Never base your studying off of her powerpoints because they LACK information, she puts questions on the exams specifically to see who does their readings.

Not very interesting, only reads the book and her powerpoints. No need to go to class, you could read the book and powerpoint and be fine for the midterms, however, the final exam is writing by the faculty and not the prof, hence, read the book more than her powerpoints.

Class attendance not necessary, she reads from the textbook and exam content came from textbook. Her lectures were pretty dry but she seemed like a nice and helpful person. She did review sessions in class that were helpful though. Her mid-terms were very easy but her final was quite difficult. Reading/memorizing the textbook is essential.

Elle est drôle et sympathique. Elle lit le powerpoint durant le cours, même si celui-çi est disponible sur Blackboard donc la présence en classe n'est pas essentielle. Beaucoup de lecture à faire, par contre les 2 examens de mi-session sont faciles. L'examen final est cumulatif et est vraiment difficile. Le cours était intéressant.
If you know the book by heart you will get an A+. Class aren't really helpful except before an exam, she gives clues for exam.
All I have to say is BORING! She gives you an easy A but she's really boring.

She's a nice teacher. Lectures are a little boring because she reads her PowerPoint slides. Everything is posted on Blackboard, so you don't really need to show up. The midterms are a mix of her slides and the book. She's also quite funny and gives good examples through her humor.
terrible

Frédérique est très drôle à écouter parce que la manière qu'elle explique les concepts est totalement niaiseuse. Cependant, sa voix est très monotone. Elle redit le manuel sur ses powerpoint (qui sont disponible sur Blackboard) ce qui est bon puisque l'examen final cumulatif est le manuel. Ses examens de mi-session sont faciles: Choix multiples.

- Terrible teacher, Terrible lectures... I realized how bad the teacher was when we were learning the basic taste sensations   (sweetness, sourness, saltiness, bitterness, and umami) and when she got to Umami she had no idea what it was whatsoever and she just moved on. Study the textbook thoroughly and you should be good. + she does revisions

She is very sweet and kind and very passionate about psychology. Really no point in showing up to class though- the exams are 100% based on the textbook content. She asks very particular questions from the book, too.
She's fair, exam are fair as well. Read the book, it's that simple.

BORINGGGGGGGGGGGG you don't need to come to class.. she only reads her slides she doesn't even look at the students! she doesn't give any extra info it's all in the book so just read the book and stay home

Hard to understand, talks in a low voice that is hard to hear, even through a microphone.  Does not seem to care about students whatsoever.  Exams are multiple choice questions, beware the final exam. Get ready to study.

Probably the worst prof I've had yet. Completely disrespectful of students, four tests with very specific and useless questions, has no idea what she's talking about (reads right out of the textbook). Very sarcastic and you can tell she would rather be doing something else. Finished with a B+

She doesn't teach the class, it's word for word what's in the manual. In this class, there was 4 midterms with very specific and unfair multiple choice questions. The final exam (take-home) was vague and she was VERY specific on the structure. She is disrespectful to students who ask questions in class and also in her replies to emails. STAY AWAY!!

Vous devez acheter le manuel du cour pour passer le cour, elle ne fait que relire les pages du manuel donc vous n'avez pas vraiment besoin d'aller au cour. Elle veut que les étudiants réussissent mais ses examens peuvent être difficile puisqu'elle peut s'acharner sur des détails qui vous semble peu utile.

Get ready to read the book and practice multiple choice! Her lectures are her reading off a powerpoint word for word. She goes over the same material in class that is in the book. She does give some hints though, so I found it useful to go to class. All midterms are multiple choice so make sure you read your book and you do the practice questions!

I know most of the comments are negative, but I found her really nice to talk to. She may be a little shy in front of a big audience and don't have that much skills to keep your attention, but she try! The exam is the book!

The course isn't too hardm it's quite interesting actually, but you never need to show up for class (which i didn't mind). She tells you at the beginning of the semester that the exam IS the book - she is NOT kidding. All you need is to read it and study a bit
Stay away if possible! All she does is read her slides. Extremely boring and not at all clear. The textbook is all you need

She is always organized and students are handed a detailed plan at every beginning of the class. The content that she teaches reflects our readings and she will always stop the class to answer our questions.

Pire professeur que j'ai eu .. J'ai été a quelques classes mais ca ne sert absolument à rien car elle me mêlait plus que d'autre choses et ses explications font pas de sens ... Elle ne connait pratiquement rien à la psychologie. Les examens sont mêlants car elle se trompe elle meme dans les questions .. Pas besoin d'aller au cours, lire ds le livre

Horrible teacher, she refuses to answer questions during exams, she photocopies textbook pages then stop sinthe middle of the semester and tell to get see at the library in the reserve but only has one copy for the whole class.  She is lost when teaching and I was never sure what we were doing.
Awful teacher. She talks to herself and she doesn't know how to keep the student's attention. She really needs to take a course for teaching.
Very nice. Really cares about her students and does her best to help and gives good hints and examples for midterms. Midterms are all multiple choice; they are fair and straightforward.
